
Install Azure Storage Explorer: Download from the Azure Storage Explorer website and install.
Open Azure Storage Explorer: Launch the application.
Add an Account: Click "Add an account" and sign in with your Azure credentials.
Navigate to Storage Account: Expand your storage account in the left-hand pane.
Create a Container: Right-click "Blob Containers" -> "Create Blob Container," name it, and set the access level.
Open the Container: Select the created container.
Upload a Blob: Click "Upload" or right-click -> "Upload Files," choose your file, and upload.
Get Blob URL: Right-click the blob -> "Copy URL" for access.
Check Access Level: Ensure the container's access level is suitable (private, blob, container).
Access Blob: Use the copied URL to access the blob via browser or application.
